==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in the 1530s. From {{der|en|fr|abusif}}, from {{der|en|la|abūsīvus}},<ref name=RHD>{{R:RHCD|page=6}}</ref> from {{m|la|abusus}} + {{m|la|-ivus||-ive}}.<ref name=WI3>{{R:MW3 1976|page=8}}</ref> Equivalent to {{suffix|en|abuse|ive}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/əˈbjuː.sɪv/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/əˈbju.sɪv/|/əˈbju.zɪv/}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Mélange a trois-abusive.wav |Audio (UK)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

